d": {"value": false, "score": 0.4524005055427551}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "API", "normalizedForm": "API", "offsetStart": 14, "offsetEnd": 17}, "context": "DISPUTool 2.0 API To foster versatility and re-usability, we also enhance DISPUTool 2.0 such that each of the processing step (e.g., argument component detection and relation prediction) can be executed as independent units via our public available REST API.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001875758171081543}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4524005055427551}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00022345781326293945}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4524005055427551}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 26, "offsetEnd": 35}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 36, "offsetEnd": 39}, "context": "In this paper, we present DISPUTool 2.0, an automated tool which relies on Argument Mining methods to analyse the political debates from the US presidential campaigns to extract argument components (i.e., premise and claim) and relations (i.e., support and attack), and highlight fallacious arguments. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00012695789337158203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998996257781982}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 28, "offsetEnd": 37}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 38, "offsetEnd": 41}, "context": "In this paper, we presented DISPUTool 2.0, a tool which allows to automatically analyse political debates from the argumentation perspective (components, relations, and fallacies). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.315376281738281e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISIPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISIPUTool", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 40}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 41, "offsetEnd": 44}, "context": "To the best of our knowledge, DISIPUTool 2.0 is the only automated tool which allows to automatically identify and classify argumentative components (i.e., premise and claim) and rela-tions (i.e., attack and support) from the transcripts of political debates in English through AM methods. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.0067901611328125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.10307371616363525}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.0067901611328125e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.10307371616363525}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 32, "offsetEnd": 41}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "The overall new architecture of DISPUTool 2.04 is visualized in Figure 1.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0012213587760925293}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.020075321197509766}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 35, "offsetEnd": 44}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "DISPUTool 2.0 Main Functionalities DISPUTool 2.0 allows exploring the official transcripts of the televised presidential debates in the US from 1960 until 2016, from the website of the Commission on Presidential Debates (CPD)1 .", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008135437965393066}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.4066696166992188e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0728836059570312e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 36, "offsetEnd": 45}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "The last two points are peculiar of DISPUTool 2.0.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.463859558105469e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 42, "offsetEnd": 51}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "More specifically, the functionalities of DISPUTool are the followings:", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003179192543029785}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.2557716369628906e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 43, "offsetEnd": 52}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "In this paper, we present a new version of DISPUTool, a web tool conceived to support humanities scholars in the exploration and evaluation of textual political debates in English (Haddadan, Cabrio, and Villata 2019). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.369850158691406e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999210834503174}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 74, "offsetEnd": 83}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 84, "offsetEnd": 87}, "context": "DISPUTool 2.0 API To foster versatility and re-usability, we also enhance DISPUTool 2.0 such that each of the processing step (e.g., argument component detection and relation prediction) can be executed as independent units via our public available REST API.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001875758171081543}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4524005055427551}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 90, "offsetEnd": 99}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "In addition to the visual exploration of the training dataset of US presidential debates, DISPUTool allows the user to analyse her own political debate to identify the underlying argumentative structure.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.259845733642578e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005793571472167969}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 251, "offsetEnd": 260}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 261, "offsetEnd": 264}, "context": "Despite the plethora of existing AM approaches and annotated corpora, very few of them apply AM to political text, and none of them addresses the issue of mining full argument structures from such texts, supporting intelligent data exploration, as in DISPUTool 2.0. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.703636169433594e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00122910737991333}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "API", "normalizedForm": "API", "offsetStart": 254, "offsetEnd": 257}, "context": "DISPUTool 2.0 API To foster versatility and re-usability, we also enhance DISPUTool 2.0 such that each of the processing step (e.g., argument component detection and relation prediction) can be executed as independent units via our public available REST API.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001875758171081543}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4524005055427551}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00022345781326293945}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.4524005055427551}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DISPUTool", "normalizedForm": "DISPUTool", "offsetStart": 264, "offsetEnd": 273}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "When the user selects one of the debates, three argumentative elements are shown: i) the argumentative components are highlighted in the textual arguments put forward by each candidate, and a label 'claim' or 'premise' is associated to these pieces of text (as in DISPUTool 1.0); ii) the relations holding between the identified components are identified and labeled to indicate whether it is a support or an attack relation, and iii) fallacious arguments are highlighted in the text and associated to one of the following 6 classes of fallacies: ad hominem, appeal to authority, appeal to emotion, false cause, slogan, slippery slope (Goffredo et al. 2022).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.5985085368156433}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 9.298324584960938e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.6954879760742188e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9707117080688477}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999254941940308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.87973403930664e-05}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 5431, "id": "27b4a513ad6dbe3e33fcc7f0372fa06202f6ebac", "metadata": {"id": "27b4a513ad6dbe3e33fcc7f0372fa06202f6ebac"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-04349796.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-04349796.grobid.tei.xml"}